I don't see it that way at all; denying that God works through man (which, I believe we are using the wrong term here) is denying that He works through the Body of Christ--<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>man</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, perhaps should be changed to the Church.  God works his purposes through the Church; through those who love Him.  To ascribe glory to MAN would be a fallacy, but also, I believe to deny God working <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>through</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> His body of believers, the Church, is also a fallacy.<br>
